; === Dragoon abilities ===

[ShadowOps_ShieldProtocol X2AbilityTemplate]
LocFriendlyName="Shield Protocol"
LocLongDescription="Give a friendly unit an energy shield which will absorb <Ability:Shield/> points of damage. The shield lasts until the end of the mission or until it is destroyed, and also grants poison immunity."
LocHelpText="Give a friendly unit an energy shield which will absorb <Ability:Shield/> points of damage."
LocFlyOverText="Shield Protocol""
LocPromotionPopupText="<Bullet/> More advanced GREMLINs will provide a more powerful shield.<br/><Bullet/> Damage absorbed by the shield won't cause wound time, so try to use it to protect your soldiers before they get injured. <br/><Bullet/> Consider saving a use of Shield Protocol to use on a unit that gets into trouble.<br/><Bullet/> The shield lasts until it absorbs its damage limit or the Dragoon dies or evacs. <br/><Bullet/> The shield also grants immunity to poison. <br/><Bullet/> Shield Protocol has two charges per mission.<br/>"

[ShadowOps_AdvancedShieldProtocol X2AbilityTemplate]
LocFriendlyName="Advanced Shield Protocol"
LocLongDescription="Shield Protocol no longer costs an action to use."
LocHelpText="Give a friendly unit an energy shield which will absorb <Ability:Shield/> points of damage. This ability doesn't cost an action."
LocFlyOverText="Advanced Shield Protocol""
LocPromotionPopupText="<Bullet/> More advanced GREMLINs will provide a more powerful shield.<br/><Bullet/> Damage absorbed by the shield won't cause wound time, so try to use it to protect your soldiers before they get injured. <br/><Bullet/> Consider saving a use of Shield Protocol to use on a unit that gets into trouble.<br/><Bullet/> The shield lasts until it absorbs its damage limit or the Dragoon dies or evacs. <br/><Bullet/> The shield also grants immunity to poison. <br/><Bullet/> Shield Protocol has two charges per mission.<br/>"

[ShadowOps_HeavyArmor X2AbilityTemplate]
LocFriendlyName="Tank"
LocLongDescription="You gain additional Armor points based on your equipped armor."
LocHelpText="You gain additional Armor points based on your equipped armor."
LocFlyOverText="Tank"
LocPromotionPopupText="<Bullet/> A Dragoon with Tank and an EXO or WAR suit can absorb truly ridiculous amounts of damage, especially if combined with a Plated Vest or Reinforced Vest.<br/><Bullet/> The shield from Shield Protocol doesn't benefit from armor directly, but any excess damage that isn't absorbed by the shield will be reduced by armor. Armor can completely protect against small amounts of damage as long as at least one point gets blocked by the shield.<br/><Bullet/> Light and medium armors provide one extra point of Armor, while heavy armor provides two extra points of Armor.<br/>"

[ShadowOps_Finesse X2AbilityTemplate]
LocFriendlyName="Finesse"
LocLongDescription="Gain <Ability:+ToHit/> Aim and <Ability:+Mobility/> Mobility while equipped with a rifle."
LocHelpText="Gain <Ability:+ToHit/> Aim and <Ability:+Mobility/> Mobility while equipped with a rifle."
LocFlyOverText="Finesse"
LocPromotionPopupText="<Bullet/> The extra mobility from Finesse can help you to get a flank or to reach the objective quickly, but be careful you don't get too far ahead of the rest of the squad.<br/><Bullet> The bonuses from Finesse are lost if you equip a cannon. Weapons that can be equipped by any unit that can equip a rifle, such as the Boltcaster, count as rifles for Finesse.<br/><Bullet/> Learning Finesse will automatically equip the highest-level rifle in your inventory.<br/>"

[ShadowOps_StealthProtocol X2AbilityTemplate]
LocFriendlyName="Stealth Protocol"
LocLongDescription="Give a friendly unit concealment."
LocHelpText="Give a friendly unit concealment."
LocFlyOverText="Stealth Protocol"
LocPromotionPopupText="<Bullet/> Stealth Protocol can be used on any soldier, so consider who you plan on using it on when selecting your squad.<br/><Bullet/> Sometimes Stealth Protocol can be used to protect a soldier in a sticky situation, but it won't work on a soldier who is flanked by an enemy.<br/><Bullet/> Using Stealth Protocol costs an action.<br/><Bullet/> The effect is removed if the Dragoon dies or evacs.<br/><Bullet/> Stealth Protocol has one charge per mission.<br/>"

[ShadowOps_BurstFire X2AbilityTemplate]
LocFriendlyName="Barrage"
LocLongDescription="Attack all targets in a straight line and damage or destroy cover. Cannon only. Uses <Ability:SelfAmmoCost/> ammo. <Ability:SelfCooldown/> turn cooldown."
LocHelpText="Attack all targets in a straight line and damage or destroy cover."
LocFlyOverText="Barrage"
LocPromotionPopupText="<Bullet/> Barrage has a 70% chance to damage units and a 100% chance to damage or destroy cover. <br/><Bullet/> Barrage can hit multiple enemies if you position yourself correctly, but it's okay to use it on just one.<br/><Bullet/> Be aware of what Barrage is going to destroy before you fire, including whatever is behind the target.<br/><Bullet/> Be careful when aiming Barrage from full cover. The soldier may \"step out\", causing Barrage to hit a different line than you expected.<br/><Bullet/> Barrage requires <Ability:SelfAmmoCost/> ammo points and has a <Ability:SelfCooldown/> turn cooldown.<br/>"

[ShadowOps_ShieldsUp X2AbilityTemplate]
LocFriendlyName="Shields Up"
LocLongDescription="All squad members begin play with an energy shield that will absorb <Ability:Shield/> damage."
LocHelpText="All squad members begin play with an energy shield that will absorb <Ability:Shield/> damage."
LocFlyOverText="Shields Up"
LocPromotionPopupText="<Bullet/> More advanced GREMLINs will provide a more powerful shield.<br/><Bullet/> The shield granted by Shields Up is small, but it may help save a soldier's life or even just reduce post-battle wound time.<br/><Bullet/> Unlike Shield Protocol, Shields Up does not provide immunity to poison.<br/><Bullet/> The shield is removed if the Dragoon dies or evacs.<br/>"

[ShadowOps_ECM X2AbilityTemplate]
LocFriendlyName="ECM"
LocLongDescription="All squad members are 20% more difficult for enemies to detect while concealed."
LocHelpText="All squad members are 20% more difficult for enemies to detect while concealed."
LocFlyOverText="ECM"
LocPromotionPopupText="<Bullet/> The effect is removed if the Dragoon dies or evacs.<br/>"

[ShadowOps_Rocketeer X2AbilityTemplate]
